# Design Token Coherence

## The contract
Every visual property uses a CSS custom property from `src/styles/tokens.css`.
No hardcoded hex values, px shadows, or border-radius in component files.

```
✓  border: var(--border-width) solid var(--border)
✓  box-shadow: var(--shadow)
✓  border-radius: var(--radius)
✗  border: 1px solid rgba(51,65,85,0.6)
✗  box-shadow: 4px 4px 0px #000
✗  border-radius: 12px
```

## Available tokens
```
--bg-base / --bg-surface / --bg-elevated
--border / --border-hover / --border-width
--text-primary / --text-secondary / --text-mono
--accent-from / --accent-to
--shadow / --shadow-hover
--radius
--focus-ring / --focus-offset
--font-display / --font-mono
```

## Tailwind with tokens
```
border-[var(--border-width)]    shadow-[var(--shadow)]
rounded-[var(--radius)]         text-[var(--text-primary)]
```
Custom Tailwind variants for rare theme-specific overrides only:
```
neo:shadow-[4px_4px_0px_#000]   hc:border-[3px]
```

## Audit — any output is a violation, fix before committing
```bash
grep -r "#[0-9a-fA-F]\{3,6\}" src/components/ --include="*.astro"
grep -r "box-shadow:" src/components/ --include="*.astro" | grep -v "var(--"
grep -r "border-radius:" src/components/ --include="*.astro" | grep -v "var(--"
```

## Rule: if a theme override is needed
Add a new token to `tokens.css` — never patch inside a component.
